              <h2>3. Hypothesis testing </h2>
              <p><b>Hypothesis</b> testing is a way for you to test on your experiments whether yoy have a meaningful result.
                The goal of doing hypothesis testing is to compare population or assess relationship between variable using sample. <br>
                Hypothesis testing or predicting are testing using statistical test. 
              </p>
              <p><b>Statistical</b> test can be parametrics and non parametrics. Parametrics test make assumptionincludes:
                <ul class="box">
                  <li>the population that the sample comes from follow a normal distribution. </li>
                  <li>the sample size is large enough to represent the population. </li>
                  <li>the variances, a measure of spread, of each group being compared to similar. </li>
                </ul>
              </p>
              <p>Moreover, when your sample data is violated, non-parametrics tests are more suitable. There are many different statistical tests. 
                Statistic test includes:
                <ul>
                  <li>t-test</li>
                  <li>ANOVA</li>
                </ul>
              </p>
              <div class="container">
